Virtual directories can be used to run multiple web applications on a single domain.  This is similar to subdomains, but in the case of virtual directories, the directory is access using the folder path instead of the subdomain name.

In order to create a virtual directory in plesk, please do the following steps:

1) Log into your Plesk Control Panel.

2) Click on the **Subscriptions** tab and then click on **your domain name**.

 3) Click on the **Websites & Domains** tab.

4) Under Web Hosting Access, click **Show Advanced Operations** and then Click on the **Virtual Directories** icon.

```diagram

```

5) Click on **Create Virtual Directory**.

6)  Configure virtual directory settings as needed and click **OK**.
